      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PET RANGER (2) looks close to a win after placing in both outings since joining the Kitt yard. Produced a good performance last start when she came from a couple of spots wider and battled on well for third at this circuit and distance. No excuses from this advantageous draw so could break through. HESHARLEY (10) has been tackling higher-graded races than this. May need some luck from the back row draw but this is winnable if things go his way. TIGERSWAND (8) is still a maiden but is lightly raced with upside and did a good job to come from this barrier for third here last start. Can play a role again with even luck. MIDNIGHT HAZE (4) deserves respect after putting a string of top-four finishes together.",
